  "description": [
    "New York Tribune We cant possibly pay the increase in rent and it will cost us even more to move I dont see what we are going to do Two ladies of the downtrodden middle class who would welcome a little less talking and a little more reconstruction work done on the high cost of living Comrade Boom philosophical anarchist takes occasion to speak slightingly of the oldfashioned idea of state socialism stating that the basis of all reconstruction should be the Rule of Com nion Consent In other words lets all be supermen each man a law to himself Preparedness is Silas T Snaps motto What with all this labor unrest and need for reconstruction Silas has sovietized his factory Mrs Snap will tell you that Silas is really the only proletariat in the firmhe works so hard thinking up new ideas Joe Hod on the other hand is all for the I W W when it comes to making over society It is the most idealistic besides doesnt it preach sabotage which is much better than syn dicalism Joes audience is Miss Linda Waw who secretly leans to Bolshevism which allows any lady between eighteen and eighty to"
